    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-09-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-09-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="40"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d40">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.34/498</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British Chargé (<persName corresp="#p_OFDAG1" type="from"
                            >Osborne</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 289</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>His Majesty’s Minister presents his compliments to the Secretary of State and,
                    with reference to the <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> of July 15th
                    communicated by Mr. <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">Stimson</persName> to <persName
                        corresp="#p_LSRC1">Sir Ronald Lindsay</persName> on July 21st last,
                    regarding the present status of four former United States Destroyers which were
                    recently converted into fruit ships, has the honour to inform him, under
                    instructions from His Majesty’s Principal Secretary of State for Foreign
                    Affairs, that His Majesty’s Government will regard the contents of this <hi
                        rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> as a satisfactory disposition of the
                    matter.</p>
                <p>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_OFDAG1">Osborne</persName> has also been instructed by
                        <persName corresp="#p_SSJ1">Sir John Simon</persName> to inform Mr.
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">Stimson</persName> that His Majesty’s Government
                    much appreciate the frank and helpful nature of his reply.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-21">September 21,
                            1932</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
